bug.short_desc: K3b crashes when trying to burn DVD ISO file
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: I tried to burn the recently released F24 Workstation image
Fedora-Workstation-Live-x86_64-24-1.2.iso
to a DVD using k3b. But k3b crashes immediately after selecting the F24 downloaded image for burning:
-- k3b(2625)/kdeui (kdelibs): Attempt to use QAction "view_projects" with KXMLGUIFactory! k3b(2625)/kdeui (kdelibs): Attempt to use QAction "view_dir_tree" with KXMLGUIFactory! k3b(2625)/kdeui (kdelibs): Attempt to use QAction "view_contents" with KXMLGUIFactory! k3b(2625)/kdeui (kdelibs): Attempt to use QAction "location_bar" with KXMLGUIFactory! KCrash: Application 'k3b' crashing... KCrash: Attempting to start from kdeinit KCrash: Connect sock_file=/home/backes/.kde/socket-eule/kdeinit4__0 KCrash: Attempting to start directly KCrash failed to exec(), errno = 2
Using brasero burns the image without flaw. Burning data files with k3b succeeds too.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): k3b-2.0.3-8.fc24.x86_64
How reproducible:
always Steps to Reproduce: 1.See description 2. 3.
Actual results: K3b crashes
Expected results: The image will be burned
Additional info:
Crashed here too when trying to burn Win10 ISO file. I have up-to-date k3b-2.0.3-8.fc24.x86_64 package installed.
Created attachment 1190141 Debug log from K3B
This package has changed ownership in the Fedora Package Database. Reassigning to the new owner of this component.

I thought this should be fixed with latest adwaita-qt-0.4-3
If not, please post a new backtrace.

Created attachment 1227802 k3b backtrace on Fedora 24
k3b crashes on Fedora 24 with adwaita-qt-0.4-3, too. It occurs when Idouble-clicke an iso image or select "Burn image" and then select an iso image file.
adwaita-qt-0.4-3.fc24.x86_64 k3b-2.0.3-11.fc24.x86_64 kernel-4.8.10-200.fc24.x86_64

(In reply to Edgar Hoch from comment #7) > Created attachment 1227802 [details] > k3b backtrace on Fedora 24 > > k3b crashes on Fedora 24 with adwaita-qt-0.4-3, too. > It occurs when Idouble-clicke an iso image or select "Burn image" and then > select an iso image file. > > adwaita-qt-0.4-3.fc24.x86_64 > k3b-2.0.3-11.fc24.x86_64 > kernel-4.8.10-200.fc24.x86_64
Still dies on f25 with
kernel-4.8.12-300.fc25.x86_64 adwaita-qt-0.4-3.fc25.x86_64 k3b-2.0.3-11.fc25.x86_64

Created attachment 1227888 session script for comment #8
strace session script for comment #8 Fedora 25, kernel-4.8.12-300.fc25.x86_64,k3b-2.0.3-11.fc25.x86_64, adwaita-qt-0.4-3.fc25.x86_64

Going through the k3b backtrace reporter, I see duplicates at bugs.kde.org, such as 349799, 348863, 364185 and 363150.
While the former three refer to adwaita-qt, the latter tells:
| Hi northon_patrick3, | | Please try k3b master https://github.com/KDE/k3b if still crashed | please let me know, thanks a lot! | | Regards, | Leslie Zhai
| Comment 2: | I can confirm it is fixed. | | Thanks, best regards.
And about the k3b devs that only point at adwaita-qt, has it been reported to the adwaita-qt devs and where?
Besides *this* bug? It's assigned to adwaita-qt (and it's upstream maintainer is also fedora's package owner).

No, I wonder whether any of the bug reporters at bugs.kde.org have reported the problem to the adwaita-qt dev actually? Several tickets that say "report it to adwaita-qt". No link, no reply, no tracker ticket.
The %changelog doesn't mention any fix. And the various crash reports are much newer than the build of adwaita-qt.
